cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CR

This paper deals with Description Logics (DLs), which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves reasoning and decision-making, which are topics covered in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the use of DLs in databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) is relevant to the paper. Finally, the paper involves complexity analysis, which falls under cs.CR (Computational Complexity).
